<\/li><li class=\"li\"><span class=\"dt\">glint<\/span> <span class=\"dd\">to give small bright flashes of reflected light:<ul class=\"examples\" hclass=\"examples\" htag=\"ul\"><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">The blade of the knife glinted in the darkness.<\/span><\/li><\/ul><\/span><\/li><\/ul><span class=\"patterns\">Patterns<\/span><ul class=\"bullet\"><li class=\"li\">to shine\/\u200bgleam\/\u200bsparkle\/\u200bglisten\/\u200bshimmer\/\u200bglitter\/\u200bglint <span class=\"eb\">on<\/span> something<\/li><li class=\"li\">to shine\/\u200bgleam\/\u200bglow\/\u200bsparkle\/\u200bglisten\/\u200bshimmer\/\u200bglitter\/\u200btwinkle\/\u200bglint <span class=\"eb\">with<\/span> something<\/li><li class=\"li\">to shine\/\u200bgleam\/\u200bsparkle\/\u200bglisten\/\u200bshimmer\/\u200bglitter\/\u200bglint <span class=\"eb\">in the sunlight<\/span><\/li><li class=\"li\">to shine\/\u200bgleam\/\u200bglisten\/\u200bshimmer\/\u200bglitter\/\u200bglint <span class=\"eb\">in the moonlight<\/span><\/li><li class=\"li\">the <span class=\"eb\">stars<\/span> shine\/\u200bsparkle\/\u200bglitter\/\u200btwinkle<\/li><li class=\"li\">somebody\u2019s <span class=\"eb\">eyes<\/span> shine\/\u200bgleam\/\u200bglow\/\u200bsparkle\/\u200bglisten\/\u200bglitter\/\u200btwinkle\/\u200bglint<\/li><li class=\"li\">to shine\/\u200bgleam\/\u200bglow\/\u200bglitter <span class=\"eb\">brightly<\/span><\/li><li class=\"li\">to shine\/\u200bgleam\/\u200bglow\/\u200bshimmer <span class=\"eb\">softly<\/span><\/li><\/ul><\/span><\/div><div class=\"coll\"><div class=\"box\"><span>Oxford Collocations Dictionary<\/span><\/div><span class=\"body\"><span class=\"p\"><span class=\"eb\">Shimmer<\/span> is used with these nouns as the subject: <ul class=\"collocs_list\"><li class=\"li\" bord=\"n\">haze<\/li><li class=\"li\" bord=\"n\">sunlight<\/li><\/ul><\/span><\/span><\/div>     <\/li><\/div>","meanDetailEng":"to shine with a soft light that seems to move slightly","antonym":"dullness","exam